The paper presents a framework and algorithm for autonomous learning in machines, which involves reinforcement learning and exploration. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also involves experiments with a real humanoid robot, which suggests that it could be relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as well. Finally, the paper discusses the computational efficiency of the algorithm, which could be relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
